Inside the World\'92s Largest Programming Course\

\f1\b0 \
This course delves into the techniques and technologies employed to develop and administer the world's largest programming course, Python for Everybody, which is available on numerous platforms such as Coursera, edX, and the Internet, and is taught on various campuses globally through different LMS systems. A publisher-like methodology is employed to teach courses at such a large scale, involving the construction of reusable materials and tools that can be incorporated into any LMS using LTI and Common Cartridge standards. The approach views a course as more of a book, complete with corresponding static and interactive resources. These elements are loaded into a Learning Object Repository to generate an environment similar to MyMathLab and are made available on the internet and readily integrated into an LMS. The software utilized in the creation of these educational resources is known as Tsugi, and we will examine its functionality and some of the MOOCs that rely on it.\
