\cf0 In this course we will take a look at the technologies and approaches that used to create and run the world's largest programming course.  Python for Everybody (www.py4e.com) is taught on Coursera, edX, on the web, and on hundreds of campuses around the world in a wide range of LMS systems.  To teach courses at this scale, we follow a publisher-like approach.  We build reusable materials and tools that can easily be integrated into any LMS using the LTI and Common Cartridge standards.  The approach thinks of a course more like a book - with associated static and interactive assets.  These assets are put into a Learning Object Repository to create a MyMathLab like environment and make them available on the web and ready for integration into an LMS.  The software that enables the creation of these teaching resources is called Tsugi.  We will look at how Tsugi works and some of the MOOCs that use Tsugi.\
